ExecDesc.value: Adobe Acrobat and Reader CoolType.dll Stack Buffer Overflow

EngDesc.value: A code execution vulnerability exists in Adobe Acrobat and Reader. The vulnerability is due to a stack-based buffer overflow error within the CoolType.dll module when handling PDF files containing TTF fonts. Remote attackers could exploit this vulnerability by enticing target users to open a malicious PDF document. Successful exploitation would result in arbitrary code execution in the context of the logged on user.
